Title : Picture Paris
Text : {{Use mdy dates|date=August 2016}}
'''''Picture Paris''''' is a 2012 short [[HBO]] film about a suburban woman with an empty nest who exhibits a passion for Paris. The film was written and directed by [[Brad Hall]], starred [[Julia Louis-Dreyfus]] and [[Gr√©gory Fitoussi]] and was shot in Paris in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/when-tv-vets-make-an-indie-short-julia-louis-dreyfus-and-brad-hall-talk-picture-paris|title=When TV Vets Make an Indie Short: Julia Louis-Dreyfus and Brad Hall Talk "Picture Paris"|accessdate=April 29, 2014|date=February 3, 2012|publisher=[[Indie Wire]]|author=Greene, Steve}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/entertainment/tv/z-on-tv-blog/bal-julia-louis-dreyfus-hbo-picture-paris-20121217,0,5712414.story|title=Julia Louis-Dreyfus delights in HBO's 'Picture Paris'|accessdate=April 29, 2014|date=December 18, 2012|work=[[Baltimore Sun]]|author=Zurawik, David}}</ref> It was entered into the 2012 [[Tribeca Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/cynthia-ellis/brad-hall-julia-louis-dreyfus-picture-paris_b_1456561.html|title=Interview: Brad Hall and Julia Louis-Dreyfus Picture Paris|accessdate=April 29, 2014|date=April 27, 2012|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|author=Ellis, Cynthia}}</ref>

